                        <provenance>The manuscript had belonged to a Tābot of Fǝlsatā, probably in the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> area, see <ref target="#a2"/>. 
                            It was then taken by
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros</persName> and brought to <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>. 
                            From there, it was looted by the British <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName> expedition in <date>1868</date>.</provenance>
